## Software Architecture
- Use Domain Driven Design (DDD) and Onion Architecture
- Keep dependencies pointing inward: UI/API → Application → Domain; Infrastructure depends on Application/Domain, never the reverse
- Domain model stays persistence-agnostic: no EF Core attributes or database concerns in `Domain/`
- Prefer explicit boundaries: `Domain/`, `Application/`, `Infrastructure/`, `Api/` (or similar) with clear contracts between layers
- Cross-cutting concerns live at the edges (logging, auth, persistence), not in the Domain layer

## Security (Zero Trust)
- Never trust network location: authenticate/authorize every request (including internal calls)
- Least privilege by default: scope tokens/roles/claims to the minimum needed
- Treat all inputs as untrusted: validate DTOs at the boundary; domain invariants enforced in the domain model
- Observability: include correlation/request id in logs and propagate it across service boundaries